	   <tr><td colspan=2>yes, that's where "numb the dead" comes in - numb the dead = undead harmony.<br><br>i tried this technique last weekend, and here are the results:<br><br>on a successful pull (i.e., just got 1 spec), i usually spent about 1/2 bub on numbing by the time i finally pulled it with dark.&nbsp;&nbsp;spook the dead worked about 75% of the time, and between that and keeping the thing dotted, i ended up with about 1 bub of mana left after the fight, though my health was in pretty decent shape.<br><br>on a bad pull (i.e., numb the dead failed and caused agro), i wouldn't even bother trying to turn it into FD pull, i would just FD until they went away.  if FD failed, i ran to sro zone (sow comes in handy here).<br><br>but overall, it worked, but with the amount of time you spend, you're better off (as the person above stated) partnering with a cleric.  the sk + cleric combo here is very ideal as the cleric at lvl 35 has a (better) undead fear, and you can use yours for backup.  pulling is pretty much the same, unless you have a druid pull (but then there's a third person to divide the experience with).<br><br>GL to you all.<br>&nbsp;<br>benedrac<br>grimstalker<br>0--{=========-</td></tr>
